desc: The truth is.. I‚Äôve hated this fridge for the 7 years since we‚Äôve had this house ü•≤. Side-by-side fridges are my least favorite fridge layout, because both the freezer and the fridge compartments are extremely narrow, yet deep. Thus, everything gets lost in the Narnia depths in the back of the fridge. üò≠ Because of my hatred for this fridge, I refused to buy the nicer organizers which would (and have) ultimately made my life easier. I probably would have saved a ton of money because food always got lost and went bad.  Recently, I decided to change my outlook, because this fridge has been good to us and she still (mostly) works fine.  I measured all of the areas meticulously and even made a written diagram of how I would store everything. Then I set out to find the right organizers to fit the dimensions and make the best use of the space. These are the results of that effort.  I‚Äôm so happy with how everything turned out! Now I that I can see what we have and everything has a specific location, I won‚Äôt have strawberry containers lost in the Narnia realm of my fridge üòÖ I only wish I‚Äôd done this years ago!  As a mama, I‚Äôm all about making my life easier and I won‚Äôt be shamed about that. I do most of the shopping and food prep in our family and this will make my life so much easier and was worth the expense. So if this is not for you, that‚Äôs fine, but my mind will not be swayed.
